  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "H2O is vulnerable to stored XSS vulnerability which can lead to a Local File Include attack.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2023-6013 affects H2O-3, an AI platform component; the vuln is a network-accessible web vulnerability (XSS leading to Local File Include) that can impact AI software stacks used for model building/deployment. This is a security flaw in software components used in GP AI systems, with explicit CVE and CVSS signals."
